authorization2star  aThis monograph is devoted to the creation of a comprehensive formalism for quantitative description of polarized modes’ linear interaction in modern single-mode optic fibers. The theory of random connections between polarized modes, developed in the monograph, allows calculations of the zero shift deviations for a fiber ring interferometer. The monograph addresses also the Sagnac effect and the Thomas precession. Devices such as gyroscopes, used in navigation and flight control, work based on this technology. Given the ever increasing market for navigation and air traffic, researchers and practitioners in research and industry need a fundamental and sound understanding of the principles. This work presents the underlying physical foundations.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aInterferometry. 4aNavigation. 4aRing interferometry. 4aSagnac Effect. 7aSCIENCE / Physics / Optics & Light.2bisacsh  aNavigation.  aRing Interferometry.  aSagnac Effect.1 aPozdnyakova, Vera I., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aZhurov, Alexei, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Studies in Mathematical Physics eBook-Packagez978311064530908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Physical Sciences 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023851808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Physical Sciences 2000 - 2014z9783110637212oZDB-23-GPS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE MATHEMATICS, PHYSICS, ENG